Package: shifttx
Title: Targeted Maximum Likelihood Estimation with Stochastic Treatment Regimes
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nima", "Hejazi", email = "nhejazi@berkeley.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("David", "Benkeser", email = "benkeser@emory.edu", role = "aut"),
    person("Iván", "Díaz", email = "ild2005@med.cornell.edu", role = "ctb")
  )
Maintainer: Nima Hejazi <nh@nimahejazi.org>
Description: Targeted minimum loss-based estimates of population-level causal
    effects of interventions with stochastically assigned exposures, using a
    causal parameter defined in the context of stochastic treatment regimes,
    including both iterative and one-step variations of the proposed estimator
    (Muñoz, ID, and van der Laan, M. Biometrics, 2012.
    <doi:10.1111/j.1541-0420.2011.01685.x>).
Depends: R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports:
    stats,
    condensier,
    SuperLearner
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Remotes:
    github::osofr/condensier
